A watchman was killed and goods of an unknown value stolen from Society Stores supermarket in Naivasha early on Monday morning.The guard was shot dead as his colleague watched in the incident at about 3am, said an officer who did not want to be named."After killing one of the guards they stole tens of gas cylinders and other items from another store before fleeing," the officer said.The source said the attackers ran away after the alarm went off."This was a well-organised raid but we are following some leads and will make arrests soon," he added.Residents have complained of an increasing number of attacks in the area. Two minors were sexually abused and murdered in Karagita estate last week.Read: Two sentenced to death for robbery with violence in NaivashaAlso read: Naivasha cops lose electronics to thieves in daylight robbery